author: {'steamid': '76561198044302926', 'num_games_owned': 231, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 183546, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 182748, 'last_played': 1711230754}
review:
Провел больше 5000 часов (да, с двух аккаунтов) в этой помойке, и вот 5 причин не заходить туда:

1. Фурри. Они везде, ты пытаешься избавиться от их существования, но они прутся в твой инстанс, даже если он фр+
2. Гомики (Также ЛГБТ сапортеры). Сколько не пытайся им объяснять что это не нормально, они будут пытаться доказывать обратное, через выдуманные, либо тупые факты (пример - "У животных тоже есть однополые отношения").
3. Женский пол. Если вы думаете с ними весело, то я вас разочарую. Данные существа вливаются в ваш мужской коллектив и начинают портить отношения с братками, потому как у всех начинает приливать кровь не в голову, и начинается клоунада по типу "На кого она обратит внимания больше".
4. "Друзья". Тут вы их не найдете, разве что пару интересных личностей с похожими интересами. Не рекомендую делиться личной информацией с рандомами, иначе пойдут выдуманные слухи про вас. Ну и любая "дружба" может развалиться лишь потому что ты просто решил поговорить с другим человеком, который у твоего друга в блоклисте.
5. Дети. Скибиди доб доб доб доб ес ес ес ес. Думаю дальше можно не продолжать.

Ну и как бонус оставлю пару коментов в пользу чата:

1. Можно прокачать навык 3D-моделирования, потому как большое количество моделеров находятся в врчате. Помогут советами, научать базово пользоваться Юнити/Блендером, ну и ассетов накидают. Также хороший фидбек от обычных пользователей, если твой аватар/мир находится в паблике и им пользуются.
2. Контент игроков. Очень много интересных миров, имеются красивые, функциональные, игровые, симуляторы, ретродизайн, аудиовизуалайзеры, MMD, хорроры, головоломки, сюжеты и т.д. В общем если есть есть время и люди с которыми можно провести время, то это будет хороший экспириенс.

author: {'steamid': '76561198197735939', 'num_games_owned': 53, 'num_reviews': 24, 'playtime_forever': 3084, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3084, 'last_played': 1707551567}
review:
Bien que ce jeux soit gratuit, le système de rank est éclaté, même des anciens joueurs ou quoi dise que le système est assez hasardeux.
Dans ce jeu, il est important de configurer vos safety et pourtant aucun pré-tuto nous le dit, on tombe souvent sur des gamins, des trolls, des joueurs qui font crash via des skins..
Le seul remède que beaucoup utilise est de bloqué via les paramètres tout les "visitor" rank, sauf que pour sortir de ce dernier il faudrait apparemment soit payer pour gagner un rank automatiquement soit ajouter plein de personne en amis.
Et si l'on bloque/mute quelqu'un on perd des points de rank vous l'aurez donc compris à moins d'être déterminer à ajouter que des randoms en ami, qui agirons comme des gamins dans 90% des cas.
Il m'est actuellement impossible d'évoluer de rank, le jeu étant remplis de joueur toxique vous allez forcément bloqué/mute quelqu'un.
Il faudrait vraiment jouer des mois à ce jeux de cette manière pour évoluer votre rank.
Ou tout simplement payé, mais vous l'aurez compris là encore des toxique peuvent juste payer..
On repassera sur les modos des rooms -18 ans, qui troll et insulte, vous bloqué la personne et cet enfant vous ban de la room..
A moins d'avoir déjà un cercle d'amis en dehors de ce jeux et jouer à divers mode de jeux intéressant, among us, murder, cache cache, bomb party ou d'autre truc cool jouer avec des randoms est devenu impassable.

review:
Spiel ist okay, Community ist anstrengend.

Nicht zu empfehlen für Psychisch und emotional labil Menschen. Viele denken nur an das eine. Dies ist kein Ort fürs kennen zulernen neuer Mitspieler eher ist es eine Singlebörse für Menschen die einfach zu wenig von dem einem bekommen und nur das eine wollen. Also ist euch Tinder zu langweilig versucht es mal mit VRChat.

Seit Ihr glücklich vergeben wie ich, werdet ihr schwer Mitspieler finden gerade im Deutschen Bereich, welche nicht nur auf das eine aus sind.

Nun noch zum Game:
- Eigene Avatar zu erstellen benötigt Erfahrung mit 3D Software und der bereitgestelten SDK.
- Viel Content anderer Creator wird gegen Echtgeld angeboten.
- Community Content sehr schlecht Kategorisiert.
- Hauptsächlich Avatare die Weiblich sind oder zustark ecci lastig bzw newlike gangster shit.

Tada und Willkommen im VRChat

author: {'steamid': '76561199227093963', 'num_games_owned': 24, 'num_reviews': 17, 'playtime_forever': 3248, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 520, 'playtime_at_review': 1059, 'last_played': 1711839403}
review:
At the very beginning, an old friend of mine told me about VRChat. He showed me lots of weird stuff like gangs, E*RP, people doing drama out of nowhere, and even doxing. After I saw all that, I didn't want to do anything in there.

However, around 2 years passed, and I got a new connection to VRChat from a close friend. He convinced me to give it another try, mentioning there would be a good side too. So, I gave it a shot, and it was fun. After about 9 hours, I wanted to try it with a VR headset, so I got the Quest 3, and it's amazing! It's so much fun to walk around and chill. It's also a great way to make friends!

My Conclusion, you can have fun as long as you stay away from the toxic people (as in every other game, I guess). What surprised me the most was the incredible sense of community and the endless creative possibilities that VRChat offers. So, dive in, explore, and you might discover a whole new world of fun and connections! 😊

review:
Es una plataforma social decente para su comunidad particular de elección, pero definitivamente; el salvaje oeste en algunos casos.
Mantente alejado de los servidores públicos a menos que solo quieras trolear la mayor parte del tiempo, de lo contrario.
VRChat es uno de esos juegos que son como una mezcla. Tienes tus buenos momentos, y luego tienes tus malos también. Solo depende de a dónde vayas y aterrices. Porque la mayoría de las veces, se convierte en un lugar de caos.
Supongo que es bueno

review: The carnage of World War II was unprecedented and brought the world closest to the term “total warfare.” On average 27,000 people were killed each day between September 1, 1939, until the formal surrender of Japan on September 2, 1945. Western technological advances had turned upon itself, bringing about the most destructive war in human history. The primary combatants were the Axis nations of Nazi Germany, Fascist Italy, Imperial Japan, and the Allied nations, Great Britain (and its Commonwealth nations), the Soviet Union, and the United States. Seven days after the suicide of Adolf Hitler, Germany unconditionally surrendered on May 7, 1945. The Japanese would go on to fight for nearly four more months until their surrender on September 2, which was brought on by the U.S. dropping atomic bombs on the Japanese towns of Nagasaki and Hiroshima. Despite winning the war, Britain largely lost much of its empire, which was outlined in the basis of the Atlantic Charter.  The war precipitated the revival of the U.S. economy, and by the war’s end, the nation would have a gross national product that was nearly greater than all the Allied and Axis powers combined. The USA and USSR emerged from World War II as global superpowers. The fundamentally disparate, one-time allies became engaged in what was to be called the Cold War, which dominated world politics for the latter half of the 20th century.

author: {'steamid': '76561199248120812', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 205573, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 3935, 'playtime_at_review': 194324, 'last_played': 1712436462}
review: VRChat这款游戏是一个很神奇的游戏，在这款游戏里面我们可以和不同的人以及不同性格的人交流，而对于和什么样的人交流是根据每个人不同的玩法来决定和你社交的是那一类型的人，在这个游戏里面，我们不再是真实的形象，每一个人都变成了不同风格以及不同类型的虚拟形象，然而在于这些虚拟的形象交流的时候，难免会因为一些话语去发生一些误会的感觉，无论我们是男生还是女生，都会因为这些错觉感变成游戏中的砂糖（CP） 也许这就是虚拟世界的乐趣之一 在这里 我们不在拘束于现实的事情 可以全身心的投入在这款游戏里面。从PC-半身-全身这一过程中 也收获到了很多朋友 无论是谁 愿好运永远常伴你身旁

author: {'steamid': '76561198254922748', 'num_games_owned': 57, 'num_reviews': 41, 'playtime_forever': 3250, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 2653, 'last_played': 1710855499}
review:
VRChat isn't just a game; it's a whole virtual universe where you can hang out, play games, and create stuff with friends or strangers from around the globe.

Gameplay (5/5):
There's always something cool to do in VRChat. You can explore amazing worlds, play games, or just chill and chat with others. The best part is the social interaction—you can see and hear other players as if they're right there with you.

Community (5/5):
The community is awesome! You'll meet all sorts of people, and everyone is super friendly and welcoming. Whether you're into serious discussions or just want to goof around, you'll find your place here.

Creativity (5/5):
The creativity in VRChat is mind-blowing. Players can create their own worlds and avatars, so you'll never run out of new stuff to see. From realistic replicas to crazy fantasy worlds, there's no limit to what you can find.

Performance (4/5):
Most of the time, VRChat runs smoothly, but there are some laggy moments, especially in busy areas. It's not a dealbreaker, though, and the devs are always working on making things better.

Overall (5/5):
VRChat is a blast! Whether you're a VR veteran or a newbie, you'll love diving into this virtual world. It's a place where you can be yourself, meet new friends, and let your imagination run wild.

Pros:
- Super fun and immersive VR experience
- Friendly and diverse community
- Endless creative possibilities
- Regular updates and improvements

Cons:
- Some lag and performance issues
- Quality of user-created content can vary

Final Verdict:
VRChat is a must-try for anyone with a VR headset. It's like stepping into a whole new world where anything is possible. So grab your headset, jump in, and get ready for an unforgettable adventure in VRChat!

review:
If you want to touch more grass but dont have time to then I have a solution!
Here is a recipe for edible grass.

RECIPE:
Ingredients:
1 egg
30g corn syrup
12g sugar
25g flour
5g (1tsp) baking powder
Gel color

STEPS:
1. Whisk together egg, sugar, and corn syrup in a medium-sized bowl.
2. Sift flour and baking powder into the wet ingredients. Whisk to combine.
3. Pour into a shallow microwave safe dish and microwave for 90-120 seconds.
4. Immediately turn dish upside down and let cool on a wire rack
5. Once cooled, pull out moss and it’s ready to use.

author: {'steamid': '76561199100747520', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 16, 'playtime_forever': 222, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 222, 'last_played': 1667566108}
review:
너가 심연을 들여다보면 심연도 널 들여다볼것이다.

유튜버들이 보여준 세상은 심연의 극히 일부였고 

그저 코로나때 외로웠을 뿐이였던 나는 평범하게 아름다운 맵과 그곳에서 다른 외국인 또는 한국인과 대화를 하고싶었을 터인데...

그런 나의 상상과는 달리 내 눈에 빛힌 현실은 상상이 망상에 불과하였음을 증명하였구나.

 내 눈에 빛힌 이들은  여자아바타를 낀체 자기자신을 부정하며 자신을 개조한 마치

다크소울의 망자가 떠오르는 심연에 잠식된자들 뿐이로구나....

나는 이것이 모든것임을 받아들이지 못한체 부정하며 정상인을 찾고 또 찾았으나

그심연은 너무도 흉측하고 기괴하여 보는 나조차도 두려웠기에....

그 심연을 보는 나조차드 그들과 같아질 것 같았기에 이 현실아닌 현실에 빠져들면 가망이 없어지기에 

이 글을 보는 너는 깊은 심연을 들여다보지말고 얕은 물근체에 기웃거리지말고

호기심이 생겨도 발을 담그지말고 

감당하기힘든 사실을 알려 하지도말거라

만약 심연의 망자들이 너를 끌어당기려해도 필사적으로 뿌리치며 도망쳐라....

이건 주의사항이 아닌 심연을 경험하고 심연을 들여다본 이곳에 대한 환상을 가진

그저 상상을 했을 뿐인 경험자의 경고이다.

author: {'steamid': '76561198383123774', 'num_games_owned': 32, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 3889, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1381, 'last_played': 1710053135}
review:
"VRChat" представляет собой захватывающую виртуальную платформу, где пользователи со всего мира могут встречаться, общаться и взаимодействовать в виртуальном пространстве. Игра предоставляет уникальную возможность погрузиться в разнообразные миры и персонажи, воплотив в жизнь самые фантастические идеи и творческие концепции.

Одним из главных преимуществ VRChat является его безграничность. Здесь вы можете стать кем угодно и побывать где угодно. Возможности для кастомизации персонажей и миров практически неограничены благодаря обширным возможностям создания контента сообществом. Это позволяет каждому игроку выразить свою уникальность и воплотить свои самые смелые идеи.

Кроме того, VRChat славится своим активным сообществом. Здесь вы встретите людей самых разных культур, национальностей и возрастов, что создает невероятно разнообразную и интересную атмосферу. Взаимодействие с другими игроками может быть как веселым и развлекательным, так и увлекательным и образовательным благодаря обмену знаниями и опытом.

Однако, как и в любой онлайн-платформе, в VRChat есть и некоторые недостатки. Например, из-за открытости и анонимности среды могут возникать случаи нежелательного поведения или нарушения правил. Однако команда разработчиков активно работает над поддержанием безопасной и приятной атмосферы в игре.

В целом, VRChat - это захватывающая виртуальная платформа, которая предлагает уникальный опыт общения и взаимодействия в виртуальном пространстве. Благодаря своей безграничности и активному сообществу игроков, она продолжает привлекать новых участников и вдохновлять на творчество и взаимодействие.

review: VR里非常接近元宇宙概念的游戏。在这游戏可以体验到赛博旅游、枪战、解密、恐怖、飙车等等非常多的内容。也可以找聊天室跟人聊天（虽然中文吧大部分都是挂机哑巴）。甚至可以跟外国人互动交流（直接去外国聊天室或者偶尔会有飙英语和日语的老外来中文吧）。 算是体验很好的一款VR游戏了，如果你有全身动捕，在这里跳舞也不是什么大问题。如果有朋友一起玩的话就更好了（注：遇到的所有人都当成男的就行，女皮哑巴是男的，女皮女音是变声器）。

review:
Pastel de Queso al Horno al Estilo Viña (Receta Vasca):
Este pastel de queso es una auténtica delicia. Su textura es cremosa y su sabor, irresistible. Para prepararlo, necesitarás los siguientes ingredientes:
570 g de queso crema (tipo Philadelphia)
230 g de azúcar
4 huevos (tamaño M)
1 cucharada de harina de trigo
280 ml de nata líquida para montar (mínimo 35% de materia grasa)
Instrucciones:
Forra un molde de 18-20 cm de paredes altas con papel sulfurizado ligeramente humedecido.
Precalienta el horno a 210°C con calor arriba y abajo.
Mezcla el queso crema, el azúcar y los huevos en un bol hasta homogeneizar.
Añade la harina y remueve de nuevo hasta integrar.
Incorpora la nata, bate para obtener una masa homogénea y rellena el molde.
Cocina en la parte inferior del horno durante 40 minutos.
Apaga el horno y deja que la tarta enfríe y repose en su interior durante 4 o 5 horas antes de servir1.

review: VRChat is a virtual reality (VR) social platform that allows users to create and customize their own virtual worlds and avatars.VRChat is not just a game; it's a dynamic and ever-expanding virtual universe where creativity knows no bounds. This social platform, developed by VRChat Inc., seamlessly blends virtual reality and traditional desktop play, providing a unique space where users can connect, socialize, and unleash their imagination. Avatars and Personalization At the heart of VRChat is the ability to create and embody a personalized avatar. From fantastical creatures to lifelike replicas of real-world personas, the avatar creation system is incredibly versatile. Express yourself with an endless array of customization options, ensuring that no two avatars are alike. Be a robot, a mythical creature, or even your favorite fictional character - the choice is yours.

review:
とりあえず入って、気に入れば居ればいいし、気に入らなければ居なくても良い
因みにVRChatとは書いてあるが、別にVRで入らなくても良いしなんなら喋らずとも良い
もしかしたら新しいトラブルや、人生にとって必要のない悩み事を抱えるかもしれない
なので、別に入らなくても良い
但し、ここは一つの世界であり、数多のコミュニティであり、表現の場でもあり、交流の場である
本当は非接触とはいえ、ここは人と現実並み、それ以上に触れ合えてしまう場である
故に危険でもあり、魅力的な場である
私は魅入られてしまった
ゆえに此処に居る
あなたはどう？

review:
적당히 조절하면서 사람들 만나고 소소하게 즐기면 이것만큼 좋은 게임이 없다. 게다가 개발자 친화적이라 자기가 유니티 좀 한다? 하면 본인이 직접 콘텐츠도 만들면서 놀 수도 있음. 덧붙여 자신이 착용하는 아바타도 커스터마이징과 유사하게 무한대적인 제작이 가능함.
하지만 소소한 게 반복되고 VRChat이 일상이 되면 그것만큼 위험한 게 없다. VRChat의 어두운 곳을 한 번이라도 보면 인간혐오 걸릴 수도 있음. 인간에게 자유를 이렇게나 주면 어떻게 되는지 보여주는 것 같음.

결론 : VR 있으면 진짜 신세계다. PC로도 가능
근데 게임에 너무 몰입하지는 말자

review: This game was my childhood. Watching content creators talk with interesting new people, and make incredible joke after joke. My middle school and high school years were absolutely made by this game. I've met some of my closest friends, and favorite people through this game. I've learned skills I've wanted to learn for years by making avatars for this game. Here I am 18 years old, meeting new people of all backgrounds and spending my nights with my favorite people in the world that live on the opposite end of my country. This game changed my life, and will always hold a sentimental place in my heart. It helped me improve my social skills to a point where I feel like I can talk to anybody I meet confidently. I love this place <3

review:
Decent social platform for your particular community of choice but definitely; the wild west in some instances. 
Stay away from public servers unless you just wanna troll most of the time, otherwise. 
VRChat is one of those games that are like a mixed bag. You have your good moments, & then you have your bad ones as well. Just depends where you end up going to & landing with. Cuz most of the time, it does become a place of chaos. 
I guess it's good when it comes to the individual being socially awkward or introverted.

author: {'steamid': '76561198174142818', 'num_games_owned': 138, 'num_reviews': 68, 'playtime_forever': 357, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 357, 'last_played': 1639182603}
review:
VRChat, a virtual reality platform, has profoundly impacted my life in unexpected ways. Let me take you on a journey through the digital realms where avatars come alive and friendships transcend borders.

The Metaverse Beckons
In the sprawling metropolis of VRChat, I shed my mundane existence and stepped into a kaleidoscope of creativity. Here’s how it transformed my reality:

1. Avatar Alchemy
In this pixelated wonderland, I morphed into myriad forms. One day, I was a mischievous fox with luminescent fur, and the next, a celestial being with iridescent wings. The power to metamorphose was intoxicating. VRChat taught me that identity is fluid—a canvas waiting for strokes of imagination.

2. The Cathedral of Conversation
Within the hallowed halls of Santiago de Compostela Cathedral (a virtual replica, mind you), I conversed with pilgrims from distant lands. Their stories echoed through the vaulted ceilings, and I realized that language barriers crumbled when hearts connected. VRChat became my universal confessional, where secrets flowed like incense smoke.

3. Segovia’s Aqueducts and Air Balloons
In the romantic city of Segovia, I soared above the ancient aqueducts in a hot air balloon. The wind whispered tales of forgotten empires, and I marveled at the delicate balance between history and innovation. VRChat taught me that even in pixelated skies, dreams can ascend.

4. Barcelona’s Whimsical Architecture
Barcelona, the cultural capital, unfolded before me. Antoni Gaudí’s fantastical creations—Basílica de la Sagrada Família and Park Güell—were my playground. I danced on mosaic tiles, my avatar twirling like a dervish. VRChat whispered, “Life is a mosaic; embrace the broken pieces.”

5. San Sebastián’s Basque Beaches
On the shores of San Sebastián, I basked in the virtual sun. The Basque waves lapped at my digital toes, and I pondered the impermanence of sandcastles. VRChat reminded me that friendships, like tides, ebb and flow. Some vanish with the next login, while others endure like eternal sunsets.

6. Madrid’s Midnight Museums
In the heart of Madrid, I wandered through pixelated galleries. The Prado Museum’s masterpieces—Velázquez, Goya, and El Greco—whispered secrets. VRChat taught me that art transcends pixels; it’s the brushstroke of the soul.

7. Granada’s Alhambra at Twilight
As the sun dipped behind the virtual Alhambra, I sat on its pixelated terraces. The intricate arabesques whispered tales of love and loss. VRChat reminded me that beauty thrives even in ephemeral realms.

8. Valencia’s Futuristic Horizons
Valencia’s City of Arts and Sciences stretched before me—an architectural marvel. I pondered the dance between tradition and innovation. VRChat whispered, “Embrace the future, but honor the past.”

9. Seville’s Flamenco Echoes
In Seville’s smoky taverns, I danced the flamenco. My avatar’s heels clicked, and passion swirled. VRChat taught me that rhythm transcends pixels; it’s the heartbeat of connection.

10. Bilbao’s Guggenheim Dreams
Within the titanium curves of the Guggenheim Museum, I pondered abstract art. VRChat whispered, “Life is an abstract canvas; splash it with vibrant hues.”

And so, in this digital tapestry, I found solace, laughter, and kinship. VRChat blurred the lines between reality and imagination, leaving indelible footprints on my soul.

author: {'steamid': '76561198301015409', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 47, 'playtime_forever': 30336, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 5197, 'playtime_at_review': 17536, 'last_played': 1712473209}
review:
It's hard to "review" VRchat as I can to others. There's no mechanics to really critique or designs to lord over like a traditional video game. It's not even a video game, it's more of social media platform or sandbox that you and other people (likely strangers) can find common ground in. Other people is what make vrchat worth even making in the first place- and that's many times harder to quantify compared to how guns feel in a video game- as it's not something in the hands of developers to really control. You can't force someone to be less annoying or change how someone speaks or treat others (not excluding obvious harassment.)

I don't use VRchat is an actual avenue of talking with other people- I've barely had an actual in-game friend until 250hrs in.  Most of my time is actually exploring niche user-created worlds that can be absolutely stunning and beautiful to explore. Space stations, Cozy Cabins, Dense Urban city Streets, Surreal Soviet-Era Landscapes and lots more that I still barely even found. I even found entire cityscapes of FFXIV like Ishgard and the Crystarium that are stunning to view in-scale with my real two eyes than actually in-game. Not to mention those shader-focused worlds that look stunning on flatscreen alone like Tree house in the shade or those fucking raves that have millions of particles all at once. Overall, I've not even touched this game's actual function but I'm satisfied at it's cheap price of paying 0 dollars to enjoy.

author: {'steamid': '76561198131737350', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 101406, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 169, 'playtime_at_review': 96758, 'last_played': 1711434887}
review:
When you first join in, just know that public worlds are like unfiltered youtube comment sections, shitty reddit threads, and 4chan combined with a healthy dose of children being edgy. Be patient and find some people you can stand hanging out with, friend them and follow along with them. Do that and you'll find your people and eventually get to the point you barely even go to public worlds. 99.99% of this game is hidden behind that shitty first impression.

P.S. if you want to have an easy first day in vrchat, go to Furry Hideout or Furry Karaoke. You don't need to be a furry, but you'll find good people who'll be excited to introduce you to vrchat without being: horny, annoying, children, or assholes. You might meet some drunk ppl though XD

author: {'steamid': '76561198045678063', 'num_games_owned': 378, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 171965, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 171965, 'last_played': 1708028183}
review:
(structuring a review isnt my strong suit, sorry if this is mumbo jumbo.)

tl;dr----

Game has ZERO moderation going on, toddlers run around in half naked avatars and malicious clients/avatars still rule public worlds. World quality has diminished (except for hangout worlds, most of them do look dope) and a lot of the more prominent world creators have ditched the game years ago. It's a very toxic place with very confused people (me included).
I'm done with it and I've finally sold my headset. I'll wait until the next big thing comes around and then I'll consider grabbing a cheaper alternative to my current headset.


Vrchat was something special when it just popped off, that's for sure. It was the easiest it's ever felt for me to meet new people and have fun. It was way less about what your avatar looked like back then, or if you were part of a pre established group. It was just random people doing random shit in the most horrible looking worlds and avatars, because nobody knew what the hell they were doing in unity. Honestly pretty dope.


Fast forward to the point where the hype died off and people started to get the hang of unity and how to make avatars. Stuff was still fun, there were still minigames to be explored and some really creative worlds being made on the regular. Later on the whole mirror dwelling thing became more prominent, which I honestly didnt mind. Overall the game became more of a chill hangout type of deal instead of exploring crazy stuff and doing minigames


Fast forward once more to the big EAC update, that fucked over mods completely. I think that was the biggest turning point for the community and the players that had stuck with the game from the original blow up.
Modding used to enable people to protect themselves from malicious avatars and animations, gave you unlimited favorite slots for avatars and let you search for avatars right in your avi menu. It let people with disablities and other impairments play the game like it was meant to be played. All of that was voided over night when EAC hit. I'm not gonna get into how long it took the devs to implement some of these features again, or the fact that they paywalled some of it behind a ten dollar monthly fee.

In 2023 and 2024 I can safely say that AT MOST, I've found a handful of worlds that were worth exploring. VRchat greenlights anything at this point, so you'll hop from world to world only to see that it's just the same prebuilt rooms that you can buy on gumroad and booth. Avatars are ripped left and right, stuff is broken and doesnt work, or the nsfw toggles actually work even though the avatars are public. Dont even get me started on how bad the avatars can look nowadays.

There is ZERO moderation, which in todays highly sexualized avatar scene is kinda... cringe? Like yeah, I love anime tits and fat cheeks, who doesnt. But when you notice the amount of literal toddlers running around in some eboy and egirl avatars that are super sexualized, you'll realize how bad things actually are. In general I'd say the vrc scene is way too oversexed at this point. I get that being a degen can be fun ya kno, not like my stupid self didnt engage in some of it, lmao. 
All in all it's a "little bit way too much" on the sexual side of things nowadays. Without moderation you'll keep running into toddlers with inappropriate avatars, in worlds meant for adult entertainment. You'll get crashed left and right, report people and then meet them again the next week. It's not a good place to be anymore and meeting genuinely cool people to hang with has become incredibly hard.

I think more rambling is of no use, so take the stuff I said here with a grain of salt. 
I'm over the game and it's community, the devs that dont care and the minimal progress that's being made.
Peak metaverse ruined by sloppy development and zero rules.
I will probably come back to edit this a few times and word things better or reduce clutter.

author: {'steamid': '76561198340663179', 'num_games_owned': 159, 'num_reviews': 15, 'playtime_forever': 7556, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5596, 'last_played': 1710999855}
review:
As an avid enthusiast of virtual reality (VR) experiences, I had high hopes for VRCHAT, anticipating a platform that would transport me to immersive worlds filled with endless possibilities for social interaction and exploration. Unfortunately, after spending considerable time navigating its virtual realms, I can't help but feel disappointed by the overall experience.

First and foremost, VRCHAT suffers from a glaring lack of moderation and accountability. While the concept of user-generated content is appealing in theory, in practice, it often devolves into a chaotic mess of offensive behavior, harassment, and inappropriate content. It's disheartening to see a potentially groundbreaking platform tarnished by the actions of a vocal minority who seem intent on turning every virtual encounter into a battleground of toxicity.

Furthermore, the technical issues plaguing VRCHAT are impossible to ignore. From frequent crashes and connection issues to poorly optimized performance, using the platform often feels like a frustrating exercise in patience. Even with a high-end VR setup, I found myself constantly grappling with lag, glitches, and other hindrances that detracted from the overall immersion.

Moreover, while VRCHAT boasts a diverse array of user-created worlds and avatars, the quality of these creations varies wildly. While some environments are beautifully crafted and brimming with creativity, many others feel like hastily thrown-together landscapes devoid of substance or purpose. Similarly, the quality of user-designed avatars ranges from impressive to downright horrifying, with no shortage of grotesque or NSFW creations that detract from the overall experience.

Finally, the community aspect of VRCHAT, which should be its greatest strength, often feels fractured and cliquey. Instead of fostering genuine connections and meaningful interactions, the platform frequently devolves into a popularity contest, with certain users monopolizing attention while newcomers struggle to find their place.

In conclusion, while VRCHAT undeniably has potential as a groundbreaking social VR platform, its current incarnation falls short of expectations in almost every regard. From its lack of moderation and technical issues to the uneven quality of user-generated content and the toxicity of its community, VRCHAT leaves much to be desired. Until these fundamental issues are addressed, it's difficult to recommend VRCHAT as anything more than a novelty experience with fleeting moments of enjoyment amidst a sea of frustration.


1 PHRASE: OKAY. NOT THE BEST, NOT THE WORST.

author: {'steamid': '76561199081905125', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 57258, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 2508, 'playtime_at_review': 47113, 'last_played': 1712491786}
review:
Constant crashes half a decade after release.

Modding scene got nuked.

It forces draconian measures on you like easy anti cheat

Massive privacy concerns rising

Half the times where the community creates something fun it gets obliterated.

Cant review, comment or rate worlds. 

Can't send messages to friends without premium account.

Can't create groups without premium account.

Can't customize certain account details without premium account.

All of that without even taking into account the massive underage user problem. In public worlds you get a 50/50 chance of getting either ear raped, crashed or sexually harassed by random children. This is an ADULT game for ADULTS. You can go to strip clubs in here. There should be exactly 0 kids in this platform, let adults be adults in an adult environment please. Worst part is that the creators are most likely aware of this but act loose because it boosts their numbers every time Christmas comes around the corner.


THE ONLY THING KEEPING THIS GAME AFLOAT IS THE (DYING) COMMUNITY. LITERALLY EVERYTHING GOOD WITHIN THIS GAME COMES FROM THE USER'S EFFORTS. ALL THE WORK LOAD IS ON THEM, THE WORLDS, THE MAPS, THE EVENTS, THE SELF POLICING... If the platform was measured solely on it's merits, it would have died long ago.

I wish I could recommend it, but at this point I feel like this platform's existence it's only blocking the path for something that could be far greater than this.

I would recommend the community. That's it.

author: {'steamid': '76561198440504366', 'num_games_owned': 288, 'num_reviews': 21, 'playtime_forever': 75952, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 3190, 'playtime_at_review': 64245, 'last_played': 1712493953}
review:
vrchatはゲームというよりtwitterやdiscordみたいなsnsかなと個人的には感じますね
自分のなりたいアバターになってそれで人と会話をするっていうのが主に多く人とゲームをするというより人と話がしたいという人の方が多い印象があります
それ故に人間関係が大事で今後のvrchatをやるに至ってのモチベ、vrを買うかに響いてくるかと
vrchatはただゲームをしたりイベントを行ったりする分には楽しいとは思います
自由度が高く色々出来ますからね。
これだけ見れば自由度が高いし人と喋ったりゲームをしたり出来て最高じゃんって思いますよね?
僕も6年前はそんな気持ちでやりました 今は後悔してますけどね
おすすめしないって事はそういう事です
数えきれない程の人の醜い所を見てはグループ崩壊も人間関係が崩れる所も見てきてたり経験してきました
リアルでうまくいかない事もあったんでそれもあったんでしょうね。でもそれ以上にvrchatで起きてしまった事が影響して
自分自身が病んじゃってうつ病にもなってしまいました。(書いている今もそう)
vrchatは今後起きるであろう人間関係がこじれてもそれに絶対屈しない精神があればどんなゲームよりも楽しめるゲームになると思います

author: {'steamid': '76561199180006186', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 258, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 214, 'last_played': 1708564319}
review:
VRChat, is a good game, though don't be surprised to find a bunch of eight year olds screaming and whining. 

I've only played three hours of VRChat (At the time of me writing this), and have barely scratched the surface of this game, so don't think I know everything about this game, I don't. I've tried to avoid worlds that have stupid people on them, (mostly eight year olds) but it's incredibly hard. This game is great, though it has its pros and cons, so here are some that bother me:

SO many really young kids, who got a Quest 2 for their birthday, fooling their parents into letting them play VRChat. 

A LOT of LGBTQ+ members, I'm not being rude, I just know that I didn't expect it, so PARENTS be aware that this game isn't always made for kids. You will find two anime girls kissing on a balcony, or two dogs (Or ten) sleeping together. Even without the LGBTQ+ Members, this game still ISN'T made for kids, I joined a public world, and found a nude anime girl. It was literally the third world I went to, COUNTING the world you first spawn in. 

This game isn't awful, but it isn't amazing in my personal opinion. Now keep in mind, I HAVEN'T played the VR version of this game, I only play on my PC, so a lot of the awe that many have and talk about, I don't because I don't have to turn my in real life head, or move my hands, I can only walk around, talk, and dance.

Now I know I basically just shi# on this game so hard, but overall I'd still recommend this game to people of ages 16+.

author: {'steamid': '76561198965705666', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 22, 'playtime_forever': 12613, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 1806, 'playtime_at_review': 7689, 'last_played': 1712481898}
review:
I was going to rate this review yes, but I have decided against it. I have over 1000 hours on quest 2 and upgraded to pc recently. I wouldn't suggest anyone tries this game.

VR Chat has become very toxic over the past few years. I've had people crash me because I was either sad or not using a eboy/furry avatar in public lobbies. A portion of this community has also become way to comfortable with themselves. I've encountered countless people either ERPing or doing nasty shit like pissing on themselves or doing vore in giant avatars in public worlds where children are present while attempting to DDOS anyone who stands against them for their degeneracy. I have large list of gross personal VRC experiences.

The company itself also added Easy Anti-Cheat into the game, though this hasn't fixed any of the issues people have had with hackers and modders. If EAC worked then I wouldn't be blue screened by hackers because they think its funny. Aside from EAC, the company itself has a bad reputation with treatment of employees and every update just seems to be getting worse. 

While I have a lot of negatives, I will say this: you can meet a lot of cool people with interesting backgrounds. I've made friends with ex-military, emts, firefighters, a group dedicated to hunting pedophiles and even an ex-darkweb hacker that was looking to repent and taught me a bit about cyber security.

VRC is not a game I would recommend to anyone, especially anyone under 18 years old. Though if you do insist on trying the game I'll say this: make some friends and stick with them. Despite its flaws this is a game where you could make plenty of friends and become a legend in the community. Quite honestly this is a game where you need to experience it for a bit then decide whether you choose to stay. 

While I wouldn't recommend this to my friends and family, just remember; as a wise man once said, "You can't let one bad moment spoil a bunch of good ones." - Dale Earnhardt

review:
Soo.. 302 hours.. i do have more on my standalone headset. (i started playing PCVR early 2023? and i had a quest since 2021.)

Good game! Though, i would recommend staying away from anything nsfw related. That messes you up (i cant really relate, i've just seen people doing weird shit before in public games).

Can be extremely funny, i mean, you can be a creator, a player, whatever. (i was a avatar creator once before!)

Though, it has alot of downsides like any game. The crashers (people that crash your game on purpose), the lag (alot of it if ur on quest) and the community. (its fucked up.)

Many places to make friends. (i have over 1k friends!)

So, overall: Good game, but stay away from nsfw and only allow peoples avatars of whom you trust.

review:
やれることの幅がとても大きい。
VRSNSであるからプレイヤーとの交流を行うのも良し、VRゲームとして(もちろん普通のPCゲームとしても)一人で遊ぶも良し、プレイヤーが企画する集会に参加してイベントを楽しむも良しとなんでもできる。
もちろん「自由にいろいろなことができる！」と放り出されても能動的に動けるタイプでなければ、新しい出会いにはすぐには巡り合えない。
だがゆっくりとこのVRChatと向き合い、自分なりのこのゲームとの付き合い方を模索していくこと(私は数年かかった)で、最高の体験をさせてくれることは間違いないだろう。

착한 마음으로 안내해주신 유저분들 덕분에 채운 것 같아요..!

아마 혼자서 그냥 했으면 10시간도 못채웠을 것 같아요..ㅜ
신기한 월드 들어가서 이것저것 해보는 재미가 있어요! 우와 이런게 있다고 이게 된다고 하면서 여기저기 돌아댕기는 재미입니다

VR이 있었으면 더 좋았겠다 싶지만 그렇다고 VR을 사서 다시 해본다..? 고건 아닌듯
아마 VR이 있었어도 90시간이 한계였을거 같습니다..

사실상 서로 떠드는게 이 게임의 목적인 것 같더라구요

그냥 무시하시고 혼자서 여기저기 둘러보시고 친절한 유저분들하고 재밌게 떠들고 노세요!
그걸로 충분한 게임인 것 같습니다!!

추천하냐고 물어보면 약간 애매하긴 한데
유튜브나 어디서 보고 재밌을 것 같다고 생각하셨으면 한번쯤 해보시는 것도 추천드립니다!!
가볍게 신기한 월드 구경하고 처음만난 사람들이랑 게임해보고 하는게 좀 색다른 경험이었어요

아 그리고 외국인 분들이랑 소통하고 싶으시면 추천합니다!
소통을 굳이 하지 않아도 대화 내용이 들리기 때문에 영어를 조금 더 자연스럽게 접할 수 있어서 좋았던 것 같아요

다들 브이알챗으로 뭘 하시길래 그렇게 오래하실 수 있는지.. 나만 또 재밌는거 모르는 건가

author: {'steamid': '76561198159179249', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 17406, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 17357, 'last_played': 1708644435}
review:
I was introduced to this game by a friend because I like to make stuff for games, this was supposed to be supportive of that hobby, which it kind of is but HOLY CRAP the sideload of absolute degenerate garbage that comes with it is almost not worth it. The depravity of mankind nearly eclipses our brilliance and I am not exaggerating. 
I don't even mind the kids, but as a mom myself I cannot fathom the levels of apathy or ignorance it takes a parent to let their kid roam in such a place without any regard to their safety. VRChat needs to make a separate age gated platform for these kids since their parents don't seem to GAF. Otherwise I do see eventually this getting shut down due to some legal trouble because the predators running around unchecked are AMOK. Try reporting someone, its not at all a streamlined process. 
VRChat is not the first of its kind, there have been other platforms that have promised the same thing, freedom of expression, creativity, creation, exploration and so on, and you know what doomed those platforms? Perversion, and unethical consumerism. P*rn addicted users get in and use the platform to indulge their habit just like drug junkies do, and scruple-less content creators sell things to them. EVERYONE ELSE GETS DRIVEN OUT. (If you are one of those users I encourage you to admit you have a problem, learn how this hurts you and those you love and seek help)
.
The developers and investors of VRChat have to determine if the income brought in by perversion is worth the short term gain, or if they even care that it will kill the platform in the long run. It's a devil's bargain. 
.
.
.
.
I am also so very sick of seeing anime avatars and hyper-sexualised anthropomorphic animals.

review:
Esta será mi "primera reseña real"... Solo pongo reseñas del palo "Messirve" o "Tremenda cacota, ñordo", pero bueno al lio:

No te descargues esto por muy aburrido que estés... Solo te encontrarás a macacos de dudosos pensamientos da igual en que aspecto, acosadores, falsos, gente que busca atención de todas las formas posibles, gente que parece que hace roleplay pero que en realidad el papel que están haciendo no es ninguno y que son así, las pick me girl que no falten, tíos que piensan con el nabo... En definitiva, una basura de experiencia. En su día me lo desinstalé pero me lo volví a descargar por cosas de la vida, como no. Las peores 28,4 horas de mi vida y que podrían haber ido a cualquier juego de los ciento y pico que tengo.

Bueno, ahora hablando del juego: A niveles técnicos es un proyecto de Unity con cosas puestas contadas con los dedos. Lo mas llamativo es la opción de "poner el modelo que te plazca", que la gente lo aprovecha para poner cosas macabras de furros, NSFW o lo que sea (Sé que existe una forma de ocultarlos pero mejor sería borrarlos de la DB supongo). Seguido de mundos robados o mal hechos y carece de jugabilidad aun teniendo las gafas de realidad virtual. Aquí tienen excusa porque tienen el comodín del Acceso Anticipado.

En su día pues sí estaba bien, te lo podías pasar bien. Lo que lo estropea son las personas. Asumo que es por falta de moderación y este juego va principalmente de interaccionar con otros. En un porcentaje alto te comerás un mojón enorme ya sea jugando solo, con amigos, o bueno capaz te llevas una sorpresa. Comunidades y gente vomitiva e irán apareciendo mas y mas con forme pasan las horas te sorprenderás de como son la peña de este juego. Si quieres interaccionar, charlar, pasar el rato mejor vés al FiveM.

Y por ultimo pero no por ello menos importante: Al ver las etiquetas de este juego me di cuenta que le pusieron la de Supervivencia / Terror y he de admitir que le queda como anillo al dedo.

review:
VRChat opens the door to an extraordinary and creative community of creators, offering limitless potential for unique experiences. Whether you're in VR or on desktop, it provides an entertaining way to connect with friends and immerse yourself in a myriad of user-generated content. But beware – this game is a rabbit hole. Play too much, and you might find yourself down the path of acquiring VR gear, accessories, and potentially draining your wallet.

On the flip side, the developers' recent decisions and changes have raised concerns, hindering the community's creativity knowingly. It's disheartening to witness a platform that owes much of its success to the support of its community take steps that may dampen the very spirit that made it thrive. Despite the drawbacks, VRChat can still offer an enjoyable experience if played cautiously or for free.

In summary, VRChat provides a unique and fun-filled space, but recent developments in the hands of the developers might give players pause. Approach with caution or consider playing for free to fully enjoy the creative aspects without the potential drawbacks.

author: {'steamid': '76561198264936099', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 1484, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 5, 'playtime_at_review': 1478, 'last_played': 1711661037}
review:
Light thumbs down, not a hard one.

At the time of writing, I don't have any VR equipment, so these impressions come from a strictly desktop perspective. The computer I played this on was outdated, but could run most 8th-gen games without issue, so I don't feel VRChat should have run poorly. I know the complexity of games isn't linear, but I don't see why this particular game should have run poorly for me, unless it was just lacking polish.

If you're looking at VRChat, you know roughly what you're in for. I'm giving it a thumbs down for technical issues rather than the culture of the game itself. How the community acts isn't the fault of the platform they use, but currently, VRChat as a platform still has great room for improvement.

Frankly, I don't enjoy much of VRChat culture, so my review DOES come with some bias- but it's not the deciding factor and I still had enough fun to stick with it for a little while. It was part of my rotation to a degree and I’ve known people who absolutely love this game, so I've seen that it can be positive for people and see the appeal from a distance. If you don't care about the experience being sort of clunky and you're curious, go for it.

In my experience though, this game worked really poorly. I swear that every time I’d launch it, VRChat would hit me with a new minor bug. It had screen tearing all the time, completely stuttered at random points, would load just slowly enough to be annoying, I repeatedly had issues where my mouse was stuck scrolling in menus (couldn’t really navigate when this happened, only fix seemed to be restarting the game), I feel my mic worked especially poorly on this game.

I could get used to the interface but it wasn’t great either; there's potential to add a lot of keybind and HUD options that as far as I know don't exist, the menus would have been so much better with some size and speed adjustments and I really feel like the game didn’t have an overhaul to make the desktop experience much better. I'd give it a pass as being made for VR first, but this game has been around for so long that it feels lazy not to improve the desktop experience. Then I’ve heard so many people talk about the developers neglecting this game and actively making it worse, I’m lead to believe it isn’t just the desktop experience that kind of sucks.

The options that were there also weren’t very thorough, so I didn’t feel I could do much about my nitpicks with the interface. If you aren't using a mic then the chatbox is really rudimentary too, leaving you stuck in place while you type and you're just forced to exit the chatbox and abandon your message if you want to move at all. As far as I know, there isn't even something like a little ping to alert you of new chatbox messages, nor built in text-to-speech, you just have to see when they're there.
You also have people using avatars that force crashes- I didn’t deal with them since I generally kept default avatars up- and it's inevitable for things like that to be on a platform like this, but also very obvious that Easy Anti-Cheat doesn't do much for VRChat. With some things I wasn’t sure whether it was the game or user-generated content that had an issue, notably, I would sometimes be flying around randomly when I entered some of my regular maps.

You might wonder why I bothered playing this game, since I had no VR equipment and often engaged with the chatbox rather than mic. Well, first of all, I saw plenty of people who used a mix of VR and desktop, or mic and chatbox- improving the desktop experience and chatbox would help those people, too.
More to the point, to reiterate, there's still fun to be had. It's pretty obvious that the main appeal of this game is how wacky it can get- though it was a double-edged sword for me. Mostly tiring. It’s one of the reasons I quit. But my favorite worlds on VRChat were the "chill" maps designed to sit in, talk, maybe play some music and people have made a few that are genuinely quite nice. It's always good to have more ways I can interact with the people I already care about, we could express ourselves uniquely with avatars and it's free.

VRChat's culture is a matter of personal preference and beyond that I think your enjoyment rests on how much you connect with the tools to express yourself here. I feel like I've seen the same brand of edginess in, say, plenty of Discord servers and a lot of people just aren't responsive or are only getting inebriated (which I find very unpleasant)- all things considered, it doesn't feel very different from many spaces on the Internet- but if you find good people to wander or just chat with, this can be a uniquely cool platform.

author: {'steamid': '76561199021643544', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 18718, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 3472, 'playtime_at_review': 3929, 'last_played': 1712461372}
review:
As someone deciding to play without the VR Headset, VRChat is still a really good social game despite the less immersive experience. Although you are more limited on how you are able to interact with the virtual world around you, if you want a good social experience regardless of how you are playing, pick this one up. The game offers endless ways to express yourself, socialize with your peers, and is overall a good time when you have some free time. And if you decide that you want to try out a VR Headset, it does make it more like you are physically there, but it’s not a necessary accessory for overall enjoyment. Anyone can play VRChat. It’s not restricted to just a headset.

However do be aware that yes, ANYONE can play VRChat. You don’t know who you are talking to behind the avatar, so stay vigilant. Because (at the time of writing this) the game is free on Steam, anyone can play without a VR Headset. Remember that if you feel uncomfortable with another user, you are allowed to block them, report them, or leave. You aren’t obligated to stay for a chat. There are many legitimately nice people who frequent the game as well as the opposite. Please do be careful about who you decide to become friends with.

review:
Honestly? The game is what you make it. As long as you know how to keep yourself safe on the internet and not take anything too seriously, you'll be just fine. You can make lifelong friends here, you can meet your worst enemies here. I personally had a great time, but other people I hear stories not so much. You're going to see some beautiful things in here, you're also going to see some... questionable things too. Just don't question it. I know this review might not be so helpful, but allow me to boil it down to pros and cons:

[b]Pros: It is a physical manifestation of the internet where anyone can create ANYTHING[/b]
[b]Cons: It is a physical manifestation of the internet where anyone can create ANYTHING[/b]

author: {'steamid': '76561198151389599', 'num_games_owned': 103, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 129551, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 129551, 'last_played': 1706676054}
review:
PARENTS, DO NOT LET YOUR KIDS JOIN THIS GAME!
This review is more about the community rather than the content of the game. I have joined this game back in late 2020 where the COVID environment was still rampant. During this time, most of the places I went to be social were closed and being a social person myself, I required an outlet to talk to others. I have logged in over 2000 hours in this game (not including on oculus, i mean meta). What I first enjoyed about this game is that I met so many people who had similar interests as I do, more than any other social gathering I have participated. To which at a point, like many others, started to get absorbed into this community. I would give this community credit in my interest in computers and understanding the hardware which gave me the ability to build 2 of them. Also meeting people from this community had me find who played similar games as I do and had game meet ups to play. This game allowed people to be creative and self taught for technology,  3D modeling, world building, game design, community building, and overall exchange of different cultural backgrounds. I have made lasting relationships with people on this game and I will never forget them. 
Now, you see that I have a disagreeable opinion on this game. The problem is, when you have a program that allows anyone to play this game, is that anyone can play this game, especially when there are those who cause more harm than good. I have witnessed many unethical practices in this game that would even have our political leaders question of what kind of society that they are leading. I can summarize this game into one phrase: this is virtual high school. Where you have kids running around saying the "N" word without consequence (getting banned isn't a real consequence), where adults act like kids and have behavior that I would send people to a psych ward. Unfortunately, toxic behavior is somehow praised and continues to build through out this community. Apparently having mental issues is something to be proud of like wearing a badge of pride. I have seen people get so absorbed into this game that they sacrifice their personal lives, dedicate and invest thousands of dollars into this game (especially to those who don't have the financial means to support themselves. this is a strong portion of the people who participate in this game). I have seen narcissists who believe everything that comes out their mouths and people who are dumb enough to follow them. Having a game that allows kids to socialize with adults, allows pedophiles to groom and commit unforgivable acts (there are groups who gather pedophiles to promote their horrific acts). Alcoholism runs rampant in this game. Parents neglect their kids to play this game. Basically people sell their soul for this game. I wouldn't call the people in this game a cult (I would not be surprised if there were cults in this game) but it changes people to the point where their original personality disappears. Just like comments in videos and social media, it does allow people to treat others awfully while hiding behind their screens and VR headsets. I could write a whole review of relationships alone of how bad it gets. Cheating is a norm for VR relationships. Having multiple or poly relationships is the norm. Running from relationship to relationship is the norm. People using "love" as an excuse where these people have no idea what love is. This VR marriage is something beyond my mind that I cannot comprehend. This game is full of people that were high school losers that got no attention and now having that social status let that power run in their heads and now think they are god's greatest gift to earth. I for one know that I am not a perfect person (far from it) but surrounding myself with these people showed that I can do better and walking away from this environment would be the best move. Good luck to those who play this game and hopefully you have the self esteem to realize that you deserve friends who treat you with kindness (Trust me, they are from few and far between).

review:
VRChat is my top recommendation for anyone stepping into VR. The community truly defines this game, and the developers' incredible flexibility never ceases to amaze me. However, the platform is starting to show its age, particularly in terms of user-generated content and maintaining player engagement. As a social game, VRChat currently seems to attract a large number of introverts, and as one myself, I find this both comforting and limiting. The community is somewhat divided between those with access to certain content or skills (the "haves") and those without (the "have nots"), creating a social dynamic that, unfortunately, makes the community feel less open than it aspires to be.

Despite these challenges, VRChat's support for a wide array of playstyles and its accommodation for a diverse user base are truly commendable. The creativity and fun generated by its users are awe-inspiring. It's hard not to appreciate the vastness of experiences available, from exploring different worlds to participating in unique activities. The creativity and dedication of the community make it a vibrant place where so much enjoyment and innovation happen.

author: {'steamid': '76561198278440288', 'num_games_owned': 93, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 56522, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 56522, 'last_played': 1703050991}
review:
After five or so years of playing VRChat, I think it's about time I made a proper review. I really started playing it during the covid outbreak, and during that time I met a lot of really cool people, some of which I still call friends to this day. It helped me work through my social anxiety, which in turn helped bring about a lot of my success in high school and is still helping me now.

That being said, there was a point where I was *too* invested into the game, and adding on top of that problems with mental health, you don't get a pretty scene. Depending on the groups or people you interact with it can be a cesspool of hate and drama. Plus, I was going into it with a toxic mentality about myself, which only adds to the problem.

So I took a bit of a break and worked my problems out irl. After getting to a stable point in my mental health, I went back into the game with a new mindset and goal; to have fun with my friends and talk to strangers. Fast forward a year or so, and here we are. I'm off my medication, doing well in college, and have never felt better!

Too much of anything will be bad for you, whether it be junk food, sleep, even water, and of course VRChat. Play the game in moderation and know what you are playing it for, or else you could find yourself in a bad place.

I owe a lot of the good things that I have going for me irl to this game and all that I learned from it, so overall, I'd say it's pretty good if you use it properly! :>



Tl;dr: VRC is a fun game that helped me with social anxiety and other mental problems, just make sure to play it in moderation or else the game could become apart of your problems.

review:
Disclaimer: I've only played desktop mode because I'm unemployed and broke and my room is tiny.

Has been a boon to my ability to express myself online that has genuinely helped me grow as a person. Runs on fairly modest hardware if one is sensible with how many avatars one enables, although it still has an absolute craving for memory (because people keep uploading models with bajillions of polygons) and some memory leak issues.

Life pro tip: disable shaders on all trust ranks. User-submitted models with user-written shaders + graphics drivers that are continuously needing updates to fix bugs = you're gonna have a bad time (e.g. your system may hard lock on you, and if your OS/driver setup doesn't automatically reset itself you'll need to power cycle your computer). This isn't a vrchat problem so much as it's just what is bound to happen, because graphics drivers can't test for every vrchat model that ever existed.

If you can cope with these flaws I would definitely recommend the game.

review:
Este joguinho gratuito de interação social simplesmente mudou minha vida!

Quando comecei, me sentia desconfortável tentando começar conversa torta com gringo, mas com o tempo fui me sentido mais livre que nunca. Esse jogo definiu traços da minha personalidade e me fez quem eu sou hoje em dia.
A comunidade com quem eu convivo atualmente mudou, mas as lembranças e as sensações daquela época ainda estão presentes, e eu amo cada segundo. Daqui 20 anos ainda é capaz de eu estar jogando VRchat shausuha. Conheci e continuo a conhecer tantas pessoas maravilhosas, ouvir tantas histórias incríveis e fazer parte real da vida de tantas pessoas. Que jogo incrivel! Vale demais a experiência.

review: 这个游戏就是能让我活下去的动力，现实中我得了重度抑郁而且开始对未来毫无希望的时候我接触到了VRC，里面的世界和其他玩家让我把所有的焦虑和负面情绪全都扫清一空，我从来都没想到我会为了这个游戏而让自己坚持活着，我现在每天都在想我要是活在这个虚拟世界该多好。但是这个游戏有点小瑕疵，就是内存使用太大了，游戏会时不时突然崩溃，还有画质优化有点差，帧数会被压下来

author: {'steamid': '76561198059724128', 'num_games_owned': 173, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 124064, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 211, 'playtime_at_review': 122155, 'last_played': 1711876251}
review:
The bad,

The place is full of pedophiles and children.
Easy Anti Cheat is probably the worst thing they have ever "Added" to VRC.
No proper modding support that won't get you banned.

The good,

You can find some cool ass people from all walks of life that you can actually learn from.
It's a great place for people that have communication issues and wish remedy that on their own terms.
It's also a great place for creators that wish to work with unity however I hear the SKD is sometimes a pain in the ass.

Summery,

DON'T LET YOU CHILDREN ON HERE!! It's not a great alternative to a daycare! 
I would personally say that VRC should only be 18+, it's full of degenerates and pedophiles and people that just wish to take advantage of you. 
Be careful.

author: {'steamid': '76561198210718171', 'num_games_owned': 165, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 43041, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 42420, 'last_played': 1708436927}
review:
Voy a dejar en claro en esta reseña que no llevo precisamente poco tiempo en este ''juego, red social''.

Llevo aproximadamente unas 700 horas en este sitio y debo considerar que existe TODO TIPO de personas y me ha hecho replantearme mi existencia, cordura y mentalidad en base a otras formas de pensar.
No hay malas personas en el mundo, unos mas desgraciados que otros, si tienes la suficiente empatía por los demás, no eres egoista y no te cuesta en lo absoluto ponerte en los zapatos de otra persona, vas a encontrar posiblemente grandes amistades a cambio de que corras un riesgo (o no) de poder succionar la poca fe que te quedaba hacia tu persona.

En pocas palabras, si deseas introducirte de lleno en el mundo de VRChat, que sea con la mejor intención del mundo.

author: {'steamid': '76561197970647767', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 16253, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 26, 'playtime_at_review': 16227, 'last_played': 1711309366}
review:
VRChat is the social application with far the most users and which supports a lot of platforms.
Since it has now also opened to a broader audience with mobile- and desktop-support, it has a strongly growing user-base.

Pros: 

- The userinterface has evolved a lot over the years and can be considered a "standard" already, as it allows layered configurations using a simple- and an advanced mode.

- It has the best avatar-support so far, since it has a lot of options for motion-capturing, eye-tracking, importing etc.

- There are too many levels to download and visit. There are tens of thousands of them, and you can probably not visit them all already.  The quality is very varying, though. As usually with UGC, a lot is low quality.
But then again, often, you can get very surprised when you suddenly find a new graphical gem or a well executed game or theater.

Cons:

- Lighting-support is unfortunately limited. Characters do not receive light and do not have self-shadowing or use advanced shaders, and pointlights are as far as I know not importable at all. This reduces overall possible graphics quality the most and is inferior to other social apps

- Avatars are seperated into three performance-categories "low/mid/high". The avatars you can find are mostly on high though, so that on default-settings, your "fallback-avatar" will be shown for others, which makes them often pointless.  

- Performance can be too low sometimes. I believe it may have to do with the engine and not always with the user generated content

- There is no way to teleport to a user in a level

- You need to find friends first in order to be able to join "groups", in order to be able to join "events". It would be better. if you could see all events on a "global event table", with notifications. Currently, events are spread over a lot of custom discord servers

- Youtube support is often buggy and limited especially on mobile platforms if it comes to synchronization. Broadcasting desktop can be done, but has a high latency and is not working consistently. Otherwise, it could be used for other usecases.

A lot of games or "game-objects" work very well like billard or bowling which I would consider polished enough to be sold as a seperate game, and other games are rather basic, but are fun in multiplayer.  A lot to investigate.

VRChat is in its state what you could consider to be the metaverse the most. 

Personally I do not get really warm with the avatars. It may have to do with the lighting, or is a personal preference. Often, the characters look too "cartoonish" for me.
But there are also exceptions. Some avatars are great, so it may have to do with the availability as well.

author: {'steamid': '76561199230755343', 'num_games_owned': 188, 'num_reviews': 18, 'playtime_forever': 6964, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 450, 'playtime_at_review': 6909, 'last_played': 1712272806}
review:
Just as a "software?" VRChat is okay, 
it's nothing special when it comes to controls or
interacting with the environment.
You can walk/run, jump,
look around and select things to
either grab and let go or
use things such as chairs, pretty basic.

But as a game it's wonderful,
there are all kinds of worlds you can explore,
there are games remade inside this game,
you can appear to people as anything you want to be by choosing an Avatar,
as long as what you're looking for is available.

Since almost all these worlds and avatars are made by the community, 
they are not all the same,
some are boring while some are absolutely breathtaking.
You can expect most worlds to be small but there are big worlds also,
the biggest a world can be is 20x20km.

Your game satisfaction truly depends on the kind of world you join and the people you meet.

author: {'steamid': '76561198042109534', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 85261, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 2539, 'playtime_at_review': 78120, 'last_played': 1712288635}
review:
There's something special about discussing college experiences with a 12 foot tall werewolf.

VRChat is by nature going to be a buggy, obnoxious platform to hang out it. Very often you get technical issues that make enjoying the game very difficult to enjoy or you find out your hardware is just never going to cut it. Further, it's a social platform and that means you're going to get obnoxious people. I feel that it doesn't matter how much work the VRChat team puts into their work, these are two constants that cannot be changed, and I'm okay with that.

For me, VRChat started out as a place to relax when my arms hurt too much from Beat Saber, but over time it's become my primary social platform. I've learned so much about technical 3D things that I never would have been able to experience if this platform didn't exist, and I've made countless friends along the way.

I enjoy this platform and I hope that both the community and the development team can continue to build this amazing place together.
